hwXdslCommon.name: hwXdslCommon

revisions.description: V1.09, Add the definition of the table hwXdslADSL1INPAdaptionConfig.
V1.08, Add the definition of the table hwXdslPortFrequentRetrainControlTable. Add the definition of the table hwXdslAttndrConfig.
V1.07, add value shdslLineConfProfile(31), shdslAlarmConfProfile(32), vopINMConfProf(33) for hwXdslAutoDeleteProfUnusedProfType and modify the description.
V1.06, add leaf node hwXdslSeltTestStartResult in table hwAdslTrapsVbOids for trap optimization. Add the definition of the trap node: hwXdslSeltStartResultTrap.
V1.05, add leaf node hwAllChActDataRateUs, hwAllChActDataRateDs for the sum of net date rates that all bearer channels operating at.
V1.04, Modify data type of hwXdslDynamicCollectTime for trap notify.

V1.03, Add the definition of the trap node: hwAdslProfIDChangeTrap, hwXdslAutoDeactivateLackLicensesAlarmTrap, hwXdslPortActRateLowerThresholdAlarmTrap. Add leaf node hwAdslProfIDType, hwXdslProfName, hwXdslPortActualUpRate, hwXdslPortActualDownRate in table hwAdslTrapsVbOids for trap optimization. Add the definition of the trap node: hwXdslProfDeleteTrap. Add leaf node hwXdslDelProfIndex, hwXdslProfName, hwXdslPortActualUpRate, hwXdslPortActualDownRate in table hwAdslTrapsVbOids for trap optimization.
V1.02, add leaf node hwXdslAutoDeleteProfUnusedProfType, hwvdslAutoDeleteProfUnusedOperType for deleting unused profile.
V1.01, add the MIB for xDSL common use.

hwXdslAutoDeleteProfUnusedOperType.description: The operation type of deleting unused xDSL profile. Options: 1. first(1) - Delete the first unused xDSL profile 2. all(2) - Delete all the unused xDSL profile 3. invalidValue(-1) - Invalid value

hwXdslLineTable.name: hwXdslLineTable
hwXdslLineTable.description: The table hwXdslLineTable contains status parameters of xDSL line. The index of this table is ifIndex.

hwXdslLineEntry.name: hwXdslLineEntry
hwXdslLineEntry.description: The table hwXdslLineTable contains status parameters of xDSL line. The index of this entry is ifIndex.

hwAllChActDataRateDs.name: hwAllChActDataRateDs
hwAllChActDataRateDs.description: The downstream actual net data rate that the bearer channel is operating at, if in L0 power management state. In L1 or L2 states, it relates to the previous L0 state. This is the sum of net date rates that all bearer channels operating at.

hwAllChActDataRateUs.name: hwAllChActDataRateUs
hwAllChActDataRateUs.description: The upstream actual net data rate that the bearer channel is operating at, if in L0 power management state. In L1 or L2 states, it relates to the previous L0 state. This is the sum of net date rates that all bearer channels operating at.

hwXdslPortFrequentRetrainControlTable.name: hwXdslPortFrequentRetrainControlTable
hwXdslPortFrequentRetrainControlTable.description: The table hwXdslPortFrequentRetrainControlTable contains information of xDSL port frequent retrain control policy. The index of this table is ifIndex.

hwXdslPortFrequentRetrainControlEntry.name: hwXdslPortFrequentRetrainControlEntry
hwXdslPortFrequentRetrainControlEntry.description: The table hwXdslPortFrequentRetrainControlTable contains information of xDSL port frequent retrain control policy. The index of this entry is ifIndex.

hwXdslPortFrequentRetrainControlTimes.name: hwXdslPortFrequentRetrainControlTimes
hwXdslPortFrequentRetrainControlTimes.description: The times that xDSL port frequent retrain. The invalid value is 4294967295. If board does not support the operation, the invalid value will be returned.

hwXdslPortFrequentRetrainControlPolicy.name: hwXdslPortFrequentRetrainControlPolicy
hwXdslPortFrequentRetrainControlPolicy.description: The control policy that xDSL port frequent retrain. Options: 1. lock(1) - The port is not allowed to go online within 15 minutes 2. nolimit(2) - The port can go online without the limitation of control policies 3. postponed(3) - The port can go online after a postponed time when the number of frequent resynchronizations on the port reaches the threshold 4. invalidValue(-1) - Invalid value

hwXdslPortFrequentRetrainControlPostpone.name: hwXdslPortFrequentRetrainControlPostponedTime
hwXdslPortFrequentRetrainControlPostpone.description: The postponed time when control policy of xDSL port frequent retrain is postponed. The invalid value is 4294967295. If board does not support the operation, the invalid value will be returned.

hwXdslAttndrMethod.name: hwXdslAttndrMethod
hwXdslAttndrMethod.description: This parameter specifies the method to be used for the calculation of the ATTNDR in the downstream and upstream direction. The parameter can take three values 0, 1 and 2. Options: 1. attndrMethod0(0) - The basic Attainable Net Data Rate method 2. attndrMethod1(1) - The improved Attainable Net Data Rate method, If the control parameter attndr_method is set to a value of 1, the VTU-O and VTU-R shall use the impulse noise protection limit INP_min0 with value as indicated in O-TPS. If O-TPS configures for dual bearer channel mode, then the highest INP_MINn over the bearer channels shall be used 1 3. attndrMethod2(2) - The improved Attainable Net Data Rate method, If the control parameter attndr_method is set to a value of 2, the VTU-O and VTU-R shall use an impulse noise protection limit INP_MIN0 = 0

hwXdslADSL1INPAdaption.name: hwXdslADSL1INPAdaption
hwXdslADSL1INPAdaption.description: Enable/Disable the global ADSL1 INP Adaption configuration. This object is defaulted disable(2). This configuration will take effect after port manually reactivated or board reset. Options: 1. enable(1) - Enable the ADSL1 INP Adaption configuration 2. disable(2) - Disable the ADSL1 INP Adaption configuration

hwXdslDynamicCollectResult.name: hwXdslDynamicCollectResult
hwXdslDynamicCollectResult.description: Dynamic information collecting result. Options: 1. noFail(0) - The dynamic info has been collected successful 2. memFull(1) - The memory used for dynamic info collecting is full 3. otherCause(2) - Other collect failure reason

hwXdslDynamicCollectTime.name: hwXdslDynamicCollectTime
hwXdslDynamicCollectTime.description: Time of the Dynamic information file.

hwXdslSeltCompleteResult.name: hwXdslSeltCompleteResult
hwXdslSeltCompleteResult.description: Selt test complete result. Options: 1. success(1) - Selt test is successful 2. fail(2) - Failed in selt test

hwAdslProfIDType.name: hwAdslProfIDType
hwAdslProfIDType.description: Type of the adsl template ID. Options: 1. lineTemplate(1) - Indicates line template ID 2. alarmTemplate(2) - Indicates alarm template ID 3. extProfile(3) - Indicates ext profile ID

hwXdslProfName.name: hwXdslProfName
hwXdslProfName.description: The name of the XDSL profile.

hwXdslDelProfIndex.name: hwXdslDelProfIndex
hwXdslDelProfIndex.description: Index of the profile which is deleted. If you delete all the profiles unused, this parameter will be 0xffffffff.

hwXdslDelProfName.name: hwXdslDelProfName
hwXdslDelProfName.description: Name of the profile which is deleted. If you delete all the profiles unused, this parameter will be a zero string.

hwXdslSeltTestStartResult.name: hwXdslSeltTestStartResult
hwXdslSeltTestStartResult.description: XDSL selt test start result. Options: 1. normal(1) - This notification indicates that a SELT task has been started successfully 2. failed(2) - This notification indicates that a SELT task failed to be started

hwXdslDynamicCollectInfoTrap.name: hwXdslDynamicCollectInfoTrap
hwXdslDynamicCollectInfoTrap.description: XDSL dynamic collect trap. This trap message is generated when XDSL dynamic collected.

hwXdslSeltCompleteResultTrap.name: hwXdslSeltCompleteResultTrap
hwXdslSeltCompleteResultTrap.description: Selt test complete result trap. This trap message is generated when selt test completed.

hwAdslProfIDChangeTrap.name: hwAdslProfIDChangeTrap
hwAdslProfIDChangeTrap.description: Adsl profile ID change trap. This trap message is generated when adsl profile ID changed.

hwXdslProfDeleteTrap.name: hwXdslProfDeleteTrap
hwXdslProfDeleteTrap.description: This trap message is generated when Xdsl unused profile trap deleted.

hwXdslSeltStartResultTrap.name: hwXdslSeltStartResultTrap
hwXdslSeltStartResultTrap.description: XDSL selt test start trap. This notification indicates trap when xDSL selt test start.

hwXdslAutoDeactivateLackLicensesAlarmTra.name: hwXdslAutoDeactivateLackLicensesAlarmTrap
hwXdslAutoDeactivateLackLicensesAlarmTra.description: This trap message is generated when some xDSL ports or all the xDSL ports are automatically deactivated due to lack of licenses.

hwXdslPortActRateLowerThresholdAlarmTrap.name: hwXdslPortActRateLowerThresholdAlarmTrap
hwXdslPortActRateLowerThresholdAlarmTrap.description: This trap message is generated when the activation rate of the xDSL line is lower than the threshold.
